{"paragraphs":[{"cues":[{"time":3161,"text":"(Music)"}]},{"cues":[{"time":25117,"text":"Good afternoon."}]},{"cues":[{"time":27412,"text":"As you're all aware, we face difficult economic times."},{"time":31873,"text":"I come to you with a modest proposal"},{"time":34325,"text":"for easing the financial burden."}]},{"cues":[{"time":36857,"text":"This idea came to me while talking to"},{"time":38390,"text":"a physicist friend of mine at MIT."},{"time":41362,"text":"He was struggling to explain something to me:"},{"time":44051,"text":"a beautiful experiment that uses lasers to cool down matter."},{"time":48627,"text":"Now he confused me from the very start,"},{"time":50534,"text":"because light doesn't cool things down."},{"time":52888,"text":"It makes it hotter. It's happening right now."},{"time":56337,"text":"The reason that you can see me standing here is because"},{"time":58880,"text":"this room is filled with more than 100 quintillion photons,"},{"time":62652,"text":"and they're moving randomly through the space, near the speed of light."},{"time":66187,"text":"All of them are different colors,"},{"time":67703,"text":"they're rippling with different frequencies,"},{"time":69643,"text":"and they're bouncing off every surface, including me,"},{"time":72518,"text":"and some of those are flying directly into your eyes,"},{"time":74928,"text":"and that's why your brain is forming an image of me standing here."}]},{"cues":[{"time":78128,"text":"Now a laser is different."},{"time":79783,"text":"It also uses photons, but they're all synchronized,"},{"time":83786,"text":"and if you focus them into a beam,"},{"time":86493,"text":"what you have is an incredibly useful tool."},{"time":88888,"text":"The control of a laser is so precise"},{"time":91024,"text":"that you can perform surgery inside of an eye,"},{"time":93698,"text":"you can use it to store massive amounts of data,"},{"time":96343,"text":"and you can use it for this beautiful experiment"},{"time":98673,"text":"that my friend was struggling to explain."},{"time":101146,"text":"First you trap atoms in a special bottle."},{"time":104401,"text":"It uses electromagnetic fields to isolate the atoms"},{"time":107361,"text":"from the noise of the environment."},{"time":109547,"text":"And the atoms themselves are quite violent,"},{"time":112030,"text":"but if you fire lasers that are precisely tuned to the right frequency,"},{"time":116074,"text":"an atom will briefly absorb those photons"},{"time":118702,"text":"and tend to slow down."},{"time":120585,"text":"Little by little it gets colder"},{"time":123897,"text":"until eventually it approaches absolute zero."}]},{"cues":[{"time":128410,"text":"Now if you use the right kind of atoms and you get them cold enough,"},{"time":131586,"text":"something truly bizarre happens."},{"time":135363,"text":"It's no longer a solid, a liquid or a gas."},{"time":138185,"text":"It enters a new state of matter called a superfluid."},{"time":142125,"text":"The atoms lose their individual identity,"},{"time":144412,"text":"and the rules from the quantum world take over,"},{"time":147239,"text":"and that's what gives superfluids such spooky properties."},{"time":151334,"text":"For example, if you shine light through a superfluid,"},{"time":154786,"text":"it is able to slow photons down"},{"time":157811,"text":"to 60 kilometers per hour."},{"time":167585,"text":"Another spooky property is that it flows"},{"time":170638,"text":"with absolutely no viscosity or friction,"},{"time":173274,"text":"so if you were to take the lid off that bottle,"},{"time":175538,"text":"it won't stay inside."},{"time":177633,"text":"A thin film will creep up the inside wall,"},{"time":180410,"text":"flow over the top and right out the outside."},{"time":184634,"text":"Now of course, the moment that it does hit the outside environment,"},{"time":187591,"text":"and its temperature rises by even a fraction of a degree,"},{"time":191307,"text":"it immediately turns back into normal matter."},{"time":193430,"text":"Superfluids are one of the most fragile things we've ever discovered."},{"time":196996,"text":"And this is the great pleasure of science:"},{"time":199357,"text":"the defeat of our intuition through experimentation."}]},{"cues":[{"time":203572,"text":"But the experiment is not the end of the story,"},{"time":205261,"text":"because you still have to transmit that knowledge to other people."},{"time":208787,"text":"I have a Ph.D in molecular biology."},{"time":211163,"text":"I still barely understand what most scientists are talking about."},{"time":214696,"text":"So as my friend was trying to explain that experiment,"},{"time":217646,"text":"it seemed like the more he said,"},{"time":220592,"text":"the less I understood."},{"time":223565,"text":"Because if you're trying to give someone the big picture"},{"time":225936,"text":"of a complex idea, to really capture its essence,"},{"time":230015,"text":"the fewer words you use, the better."},{"time":233598,"text":"In fact, the ideal may be to use no words at all."},{"time":236917,"text":"I remember thinking, my friend could have explained"},{"time":238474,"text":"that entire experiment with a dance."},{"time":241606,"text":"Of course, there never seem to be any dancers around when you need them."}]},{"cues":[{"time":245974,"text":"Now, the idea is not as crazy as it sounds."},{"time":247863,"text":"I started a contest four years ago called Dance Your Ph.D."},{"time":251365,"text":"Instead of explaining their research with words,"},{"time":253980,"text":"scientists have to explain it with dance."},{"time":256880,"text":"Now surprisingly, it seems to work."},{"time":259249,"text":"Dance really can make science easier to understand."},{"time":262521,"text":"But don't take my word for it."},{"time":264317,"text":"Go on the Internet and search for \"Dance Your Ph.D.\""},{"time":267204,"text":"There are hundreds of dancing scientists waiting for you."}]},{"cues":[{"time":270462,"text":"The most surprising thing that I've learned while running this contest"},{"time":272545,"text":"is that some scientists are now working directly with dancers on their research."},{"time":277834,"text":"For example, at the University of Minnesota,"},{"time":279714,"text":"there's a biomedical engineer named David Odde,"},{"time":282219,"text":"and he works with dancers to study how cells move."},{"time":285377,"text":"They do it by changing their shape."},{"time":287786,"text":"When a chemical signal washes up on one side,"},{"time":290605,"text":"it triggers the cell to expand its shape on that side,"},{"time":293730,"text":"because the cell is constantly touching and tugging at the environment."},{"time":297011,"text":"So that allows cells to ooze along in the right directions."},{"time":300982,"text":"But what seems so slow and graceful from the outside"},{"time":304920,"text":"is really more like chaos inside,"},{"time":307349,"text":"because cells control their shape with a skeleton of rigid protein fibers,"},{"time":311752,"text":"and those fibers are constantly falling apart."},{"time":314597,"text":"But just as quickly as they explode,"},{"time":317166,"text":"more proteins attach to the ends and grow them longer,"},{"time":319583,"text":"so it's constantly changing"},{"time":321766,"text":"just to remain exactly the same."},{"time":324764,"text":"Now, David builds mathematical models of this and then he tests those in the lab,"},{"time":327934,"text":"but before he does that, he works with dancers"},{"time":330709,"text":"to figure out what kinds of models to build in the first place."},{"time":334410,"text":"It's basically efficient brainstorming,"},{"time":337503,"text":"and when I visited David to learn about his research,"},{"time":339758,"text":"he used dancers to explain it to me"},{"time":343102,"text":"rather than the usual method: PowerPoint."}]},{"cues":[{"time":347644,"text":"And this brings me to my modest proposal."},{"time":349997,"text":"I think that bad PowerPoint presentations"},{"time":352866,"text":"are a serious threat to the global economy."}]},{"cues":[{"time":355538,"text":"(Laughter) (Applause)"}]},{"cues":[{"time":363467,"text":"Now it does depend on how you measure it, of course,"},{"time":368346,"text":"but one estimate has put the drain at 250 million dollars per day."},{"time":373115,"text":"Now that assumes half-hour presentations"},{"time":375296,"text":"for an average audience of four people"},{"time":377353,"text":"with salaries of 35,000 dollars,"},{"time":379672,"text":"and it conservatively assumes that"},{"time":381632,"text":"about a quarter of the presentations are a complete waste of time,"},{"time":385564,"text":"and given that there are some apparently"},{"time":388143,"text":"30 million PowerPoint presentations created every day,"},{"time":391415,"text":"that would indeed add up to an annual waste"},{"time":394303,"text":"of 100 billion dollars."},{"time":397399,"text":"Of course, that's just the time we're losing"},{"time":399767,"text":"sitting through presentations."},{"time":401990,"text":"There are other costs, because PowerPoint is a tool,"},{"time":406306,"text":"and like any tool, it can and will be abused."},{"time":409636,"text":"To borrow a concept from my country's CIA,"},{"time":412126,"text":"it helps you to soften up your audience."},{"time":415241,"text":"It distracts them with pretty pictures, irrelevant data."},{"time":419489,"text":"It allows you to create the illusion of competence,"},{"time":423229,"text":"the illusion of simplicity,"},{"time":425989,"text":"and most destructively, the illusion of understanding."}]},{"cues":[{"time":430716,"text":"So now my country is 15 trillion dollars in debt."},{"time":434960,"text":"Our leaders are working tirelessly to try and find ways to save money."},{"time":439945,"text":"One idea is to drastically reduce public support for the arts."},{"time":444414,"text":"For example, our National Endowment for the Arts,"},{"time":446622,"text":"with its $150 million budget,"},{"time":449199,"text":"slashing that program would immediately reduce the national debt"},{"time":452211,"text":"by about one one-thousandth of a percent."},{"time":455572,"text":"One certainly can't argue with those numbers."},{"time":457312,"text":"However, once we eliminate public funding for the arts,"},{"time":462594,"text":"there will be some drawbacks."},{"time":465266,"text":"The artists on the street will swell the ranks of the unemployed."},{"time":469662,"text":"Many will turn to drug abuse and prostitution,"},{"time":472069,"text":"and that will inevitably lower property values in urban neighborhoods."},{"time":475188,"text":"All of this could wipe out the savings we're hoping to make in the first place."}]},{"cues":[{"time":480095,"text":"I shall now, therefore, humbly propose my own thoughts,"},{"time":483336,"text":"which I hope will not be liable to the least objection."},{"time":487118,"text":"Once we eliminate public funding for the artists,"},{"time":489011,"text":"let's put them back to work"},{"time":490598,"text":"by using them instead of PowerPoint."},{"time":493619,"text":"As a test case, I propose we start with American dancers."},{"time":497102,"text":"After all, they are the most perishable of their kind,"},{"time":499255,"text":"prone to injury and very slow to heal"},{"time":501414,"text":"due to our health care system."},{"time":504231,"text":"Rather than dancing our Ph.Ds,"},{"time":507374,"text":"we should use dance to explain all of our complex problems."},{"time":510988,"text":"Imagine our politicians using dance"},{"time":513848,"text":"to explain why we must invade a foreign country"},{"time":517626,"text":"or bail out an investment bank."},{"time":520498,"text":"It's sure to help."}]},{"cues":[{"time":522460,"text":"Of course someday, in the deep future,"},{"time":526212,"text":"a technology of persuasion"},{"time":528593,"text":"even more powerful than PowerPoint may be invented,"},{"time":532022,"text":"rendering dancers unnecessary as tools of rhetoric."},{"time":535566,"text":"However, I trust that by that day,"},{"time":538142,"text":"we shall have passed this present financial calamity."},{"time":541457,"text":"Perhaps by then we will be able to afford the luxury"},{"time":544823,"text":"of just sitting in an audience"},{"time":547943,"text":"with no other purpose"},{"time":549783,"text":"than to witness the human form in motion."},{"time":554349,"text":"(Music)"},{"time":625189,"text":"(Applause)"}]}]}